Three main hypotheses have been invoked to explain recently established interspecific hybridisations among animal species, and may have played a role in the present case by promoting syntopy and breeding season overlap (
 Crispo et al., 2011; 
 Chunco, 2014): species translocations, anthropogenic habitat degradation (a derivation of the Anderson’s ‘hybridisation of the habitat’ model; 
 Anderson, 1948) and climate changes.
